# Kadamba Typography & Layout Rules

## Critical Tailwind v4 theme rule

Never redefine `--spacing-sm`, `--spacing-md`, `--spacing-lg`, or `--spacing-xl` inside `@theme`.

In this Tailwind version, `max-w-sm|md|lg|xl` resolve to those spacing tokens. Overriding them collapses body copy into ~1–6rem columns (one word per line).

Use namespaced tokens instead:

- `--kadamba-space-xs|sm|md|lg|xl` for section rhythm
- `--measure` / `--measure-wide` (or `.text-lede` / `.text-measure`) for readable line length

## Professional classic copy structure

Every major section must use `SectionIntro` from `@/components/ui`:

- One clear heading (Playfair / `Heading`)
- One lede paragraph with comfortable measure (~38rem), `leading-relaxed`, `text-lede`
- Optional actions (filters, links) aligned on large screens — never squeeze the lede

Do **not** place section descriptions in ad-hoc `max-w-sm|md|lg|xl` unless you verified the compiled CSS uses container widths.

Safe max-width choices:

- Prefer `.text-lede`, `.text-measure`, `max-w-2xl`+ (container scale), or arbitrary `max-w-[36rem]`
- Avoid `max-w-sm|md|lg|xl` for prose unless confirmed safe in the built CSS

## Hierarchy

1. Brand / section title — serif, confident scale
2. Lede — one short supporting sentence, readable measure
3. Body / meta — smaller, muted, relaxed leading

Keep copy professional and classic: no cramped columns, no decorative vertical stacking of words, no orphan one-word lines caused by broken widths.

## Accessibility

- Maintain heading order (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`)
- Ensure contrast on cream and black surfaces
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for animated text swaps
- Touch targets for filters/controls ≥ 40px where practical
